\chapter{Palau}

The Republic of Palau is an island nation in the Pacific Ocean, 500 miles east of the [Philippines](../philippines/Introduction) and 2,000 miles south of [Japan](../japan/Introduction).

\section{Pre-independence}

The islands first used stamps of Germany for the [Caroline Islands](../caroline-islands/Introduction) and then stamps of Japan from 1914 to 1944. The islands then became part of the U.S. Trust Territory of the Pacific and used American stamps until 1983.

\section{Independence}

1983 20 cent denomination of the stamps for inauguration of the independent postal service
The first stamps of Palau were issued in 1983.

